== Motte and Bailey

#slide[
  #align(center)[
    #image("motte-bailey.jpg", width: 40%)
  ]

  #v(0.3em)

  #align(center)[
    #text(size: 0.7em)[Image source: #link("https://www.totalbattleminiatures.com/product-page/wooden-motte-and-bailey-castle")[#text(fill: rgb("#2563eb"))[#underline("totalbattleminiatures.com")]]]
  ]
]

#slide[
  #align(center + horizon)[
    #text(size: 1.3em)[
      *Bailey (controversial claim):*\
      "We need to abolish the police."

      #v(1em)

      *Motte (defensible retreat):*\
      "We should reform problematic aspects of policing and explore alternative approaches to public safety."
    ]
  ]
]

== Equivocation

#slide[
  #align(center + horizon)[
    #text(size: 1.1em)[
      Since only *man* is rational.\
      And no woman is a *man*.\
      Therefore, no woman is rational.

      #v(0.8em)

      #text(size: 0.9em)[
        Equivocates "man" between:\
        • First use: *human being*\
        • Second use: *male person*

        #v(0.5em)

        #text(size: 0.8em)[Source: T. Damer, _Attacking Faulty Reasoning_ (via Wikipedia)]
      ]
    ]
  ]
]

== Abusing Categories

#slide[
  #align(horizon)[
    #text(size: 1.1em)[
      A situation has 3 out of 7 markers of "gaslighting" → someone uses the term.

      #v(0.5em)

      *The problem:* Others hear "gaslighting" and assume *all 7 markers* are present (plus their own associations), not just the 3 that were actually observed.

      #v(0.5em)

      *Done intentionally:* weaponized equivocation\
      *Done accidentally:* still causes confusion and misunderstanding
    ]
  ]
]
